# Design Token Usage

All component and template code must reference design tokens â€” never hardcode raw values.
Tokens live in `src/tokens/` and are re-exported from `src/tokens/index.ts`.

## Spacing â€” `spacing` / `space`

```ts
import { spacing, space } from "@/tokens/spacing";

// âťŚ BAD
gap: 8, padding: 16

// âś… GOOD
gap: spacing[2], padding: space.componentPaddingMD
```

| Token | Value | Use for |
|---|---|---|
| `spacing[1]` | 4px | micro gaps |
| `spacing[2]` | 8px | icon gaps, tight padding |
| `spacing[3]` | 12px | compact padding |
| `spacing[4]` | 16px | standard padding (base unit) |
| `spacing[6]` | 24px | section padding |
| `space.componentPaddingMD` | 16px | card / component inner padding |
| `space.stackSM` | 8px | vertical stack gap |
| `space.pagePaddingHorizontal` | 16px | screen edge padding |

## Border Radius â€” `radii`

```ts
import { radii } from "@/tokens/radii";

// âťŚ BAD
borderRadius: 8, borderRadius: 48, borderRadius: "50%"

// âś… GOOD
borderRadius: radii.md, borderRadius: radii.pill
```

| Token | Value | Use for |
|---|---|---|
| `radii.none` | 0 | sharp corners |
| `radii.xs` | 2px | decorative SVG elements |
| `radii.sm` | 4px | badges, tags, code chips |
| `radii.md` | 8px | cards, inputs, action bars |
| `radii.lg` | 12px | icon containers, dialogs |
| `radii.xl` | 16px | bottom sheets, modals |
| `radii["2xl"]` | 24px | large cards, panels |
| `radii.pill` | 9999px | buttons, toggles, notification dots |

## Colours â€” `colors` / `palette`

```ts
import { colors, palette } from "@/tokens/colors";

// âťŚ BAD
color: "#E30D76", backgroundColor: "#FFFFFF"

// âś… GOOD
color: colors.actionPrimaryHover, backgroundColor: colors.bgElevated
```

Always prefer semantic `colors.*` tokens. Use `palette.*` only when no semantic token exists and document why.

## Typography â€” `textStyles` / `fontSize` / `fontWeight`

```ts
import { textStyles, fontSize, fontWeight, fontFamily } from "@/tokens/typography";

// âťŚ BAD
fontSize: 16, fontWeight: "700"

// âś… GOOD
...textStyles.body1Bold   // preferred: spread the full preset
fontSize: fontSize.md     // acceptable: individual scale token
```

## Figma â†’ token mapping workflow

When implementing a Figma design:
1. Map every Figma spacing/padding value to the closest `spacing[n]` or `space.*` token.
2. Map every `borderRadius` to a `radii.*` token (see table above).
3. Map every colour to a `colors.*` semantic token; fall back to `palette.*` with a comment.
4. Map every text style to a `textStyles.*` preset.
5. Never leave a comment like `// 8px` â€” let the token name document the intent.
